---
description: Structure of ApiResponse class.
globs: **/src/main/java/com/example/demo/dto/ApiResponse.java
---
- ApiResponse must contain exactly these payload concepts: `result`, `message`, and `data`.
- `result` should represent success/error status in a consistent format (for example: `SUCCESS` or `ERROR`).
- Provide clear factory helpers for success and error responses when possible.
- Keep ApiResponse immutable by default (prefer `record` unless a prompt explicitly requires a mutable class).
